description: Police are appealing for witnesses to the crash in Claygate on Thursday night.
title: Claygate crash: Boy, 15, and man, 31, suffer injuries
title_page: Claygate crash: Boy, 15, and man, 31, suffer injuries - BBC News
maintext:
A 15-year-old boy and a man, 31, have been injured in a crash in Surrey.
Emergency services were called to the single-vehicle crash in Woodstock Lane South, Claygate, at 22:30 GMT on Thursday.
The boy and man were taken to hospital for medical treatment, police said.
A third man was also taken to hospital, but has since been discharged.
